cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

The paper uses deep learning techniques to analyze satellite imagery and geo-referenced crime reports to quantify the impact of the built environment on neighborhood crime rates. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with crime rates, which suggests it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of satellite imagery and geo-referenced data could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the use of deep learning techniques could also place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
